@ Tasty: What an excellent video montage of great recipes and you were doing so well until the very last one darn it! You NEVER NEVER EVER use Enchilada sauce for Chicken Tortilla soup!!! I've seen this mistake repeated so many times in online recipes (such as Chicken Tortilla Soup or Menudo) and it betrays the non-Hispanic identity of the person who wrote it lol!! Enchilada sauce has a VERY distinctive flavor & was created strictly for the single purpose of making Enchiladas. Don't ever use it for soups or else it will make your dish taste like Enchilada soup, lol. Instead I recommend adding 1 diced jalepeno, some fire roasted tomatoes, and at least 1-2 7oz cans of Salsa Casera (more will not be a bad thing hint hint lol) to give it a more correct & accurate flavor. Glad to see you did add lime juice & cilantro at the end though, nice touch.

I always buy Tilapia from Kroger. I wanted to try something new, so I bought this Swai fish for the first time 3 days ago. Today I was frying the fish when I found two parasites.
